description: You're looking at more than just a 1968 Chevrolet Camaro RS in the perfect color combo.  Dig a little deeper into this icon and you'll find upgrades to make it an outstanding cruiser like an updated V8, overdrive transmission, and A/C interior.

You can just tell from the pictures how well the black suits this sports car.  It started life in a tamer shade of Ermine White.  That's a fine Chevy color, but it was not going to be good enough for a car with this kind of presence.  So, it was given this deep, dark hue to better fit its true personality.  You can't hide imperfections from black, and so only the straightest and best bodies like this one can wear this desirable color with pride.  Added to this is the always cool red D91 bumblebee stripe.  Keeping the aggressive packaging going are the great touches like the front air dam, D80 rear spoiler, and the power bulge cowl hood.  Chrome bumpers flank the car at both ends, adding a shiny bit of punctuation to the dark storyline.  But without a doubt, it's those concealed headlights from the RS package (now with electric doors) that will gain all the attention.

Just like the exterior, the blue interior was changed to a new more aggressive style.  Now the red exterior stripe is just a cool preview for the color inside, which makes for a terrific uniform package. As mentioned before, this classic was meant to be a true cruiser, so items like the stereo been upgraded to an AM/FM/cassette deck.  And the feature everyone will love the most is the factory air conditioning still pumping through the Astro ventilation system.  But the best treats are reserved for the driver.  You get a comfortable center console with the iconic horseshoe shifter, comfortable bucket seats, and a grippy three-spoke factory steering wheel.

Under the hood is a stout 350 cubic-inch V8. It's a newer small block, so it has far fewer miles on it and runs smoother than many of the other classics out there.  Plus, there are many affordable upgrades for this motor that can be added in a matter of hours.  In fact, this one already comes with plenty of car show worthy shine on the air cleaner and valve covers.  Plus, there's an Edelbrock intake and four-barrel carburetor for added performance.  So the dual exhaust has a hardy V8 growl.  The engine was not the only part of the package that was updated.  There's also a 700R4 four-speed automatic transmission w/overdrive.  Combine that with power steering and BF Goodrich T/As on iconic Rally wheels, and you have an exceptional cruising package.
You're looking at a Camaro with all the right upgrades for show AND go.  A total package like this never stays long in our showroom.  Call today!!!

description: For sale in our Orlando Florida  showroom is a restored 1968 Chevrolet Camaro. It is often that the first generation of a model is considered the best. In the case of the Camaro it is certainly the most desirable and a lot would argue the most attractive. '68 offered a few changes from '67 including the addition of the Astro-Ventilation system which eliminated the need for vent windows. The mono-leaf rear spring set-up was upgraded to a multi-leaf set up for higher performance models. This particular example is an 327  V8  which boasts a 275 horsepower mated a powerglide automatic  transmission. Both engine and transmission are numbers matching according to the consignor. The neat thing about this Camaro is that it has only had two  owners. The car was restored with originality in mind and is fully documented and has protecto Ã¢?"plate and original bill of sale and original California Tags.  This is a car that is equipped with hub caps, seat belts, vinyl interior, and radial ply tires. One of the coolest features might be the originality of this beautiful 1968 Camaro.  Outside the car is finished in a very sharp Tuxedo Black  . The wheels are color matched and with the original hub caps it has a very classic look. The interior is white vinyl upholstery with black carpet, and headliner. This is a beautiful all original Camaro with a neat history and a very sharp color combination. If you're ready to stand out at car shows and drive down the road in a classic muscle car, this one is for you. You can see this vehicle in greater detail, including HD video, at www.GatewayClassicCars.com. New to our Benicia showroom is this gorgeous 1968 Chevrolet Camaro 2 Door Coupe with black exterior paint, a black leather interior. The interior has been replaced with custom made leather bucket seat, front and back. You absolutely have to see this one in person to truly appreciate it.

The current owner of this 1968 Chevrolet Camaro informs us that he invested over $100,000 into transforming this beast of a muscle car into the nicest Pro Touring classics we have ever seen. Many panels have been reproduced with carbon fiber in an effort to reduce as much weight as possible. It has a one of a kind carbon fiber intake with twin throttle bodies, as well as a carbon fiber hood, cowl, front clip, wheel wells, deck lid, a smoothed fire wall, and far too many other performance customizations to list. This one is lightning fast with incredible handling and it performs like a modern high-end sport cars.

Additionally, this 1968 Chevrolet Camaro has a luxury feel throughout with four leather/Alacantra bucket seats, an awesome instrument cluster and carbon fiber galore. From the flawless body to the high-end custom paint to the intelligent wiring under the hood, this one is show ready and really stands out in a crowd. At the current asking price, it would be almost impossible to find a more refined example.

Overall, this 1968 Chevrolet Camaro is one of the nicest Pro Touring builds we’ve ever seen and this vehicle is going to appeal to a wide variety of collectors. Given this car’s excellent desirability and how well it performs, this one is an absolute steal and it will find a new home quickly. So don’t wait around, come see this amazing muscle car today!
